---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How quickly can you get to a broken garage door in Cranbourne?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Same-day in most cases if you call before 2pm, Monday to Saturday. Cranbourne 3977 (including East, West, North and Park) is our home turf — we're based here, the van is stocked for the most common Casey-area failures, and most jobs are dispatched within an hour of the phone call." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What's the most common garage door failure in Cranbourne East / West / North?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A broken extension or torsion spring on an 8–14 year-old builder-grade double sectional. The estates released between 2010 and 2018 used the cheapest spring spec the door manufacturers offered — 10,000-cycle springs on a door cycled 4–8 times a day go in around year 7–10. We replace these with 25,000-cycle commercial-grade springs as a standard upgrade; the price difference is small and the next failure is 15+ years away." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can you match the colour of my existing Colorbond roof?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. All major brands (B&D, Steel-Line, Dominator, Centurion) supply doors in the full Colorbond range plus the popular custom colours (Surfmist, Monument, Basalt, Woodland Grey, Dune, Shale Grey). On a new install we colour-match to the roof or guttering, whichever the front-of-house elevation reads off. For repairs to one or two panels on an existing door, we colour-match to the existing door panels." }}
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Garage Doors Cranbourne | Install & Repair | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Garage door installation, repair and motor replacement in Cranbourne — including Cranbourne East, West, North and Park. Broken-spring emergency call-out, quiet belt-drive motors, new Colorbond sectional and roller doors."
  canonical="https://cranbournegaragedoorco.com.au/cranbourne/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Cranbourne &middot; Cranbourne East &middot; West &middot; North &middot; Park</span>
      <h1>Garage doors in <span class="accent">Cranbourne</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Cranbourne is our home suburb &mdash; 3977 and the four estate suburbs
        (Cranbourne East, West, North, Park) make up most of our weekly work.
        Mix of new-estate builder-grade doors hitting their 8&ndash;15 year
        failure curve, and established Cranbourne township properties with
        tilt and side-hung doors due for replacement.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a fixed quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Cranbourne</span>
      <h2>The Cranbourne garage door story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Two distinct property types.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>The growth-corridor estates</strong> (Cranbourne East, West,
          North, Park &mdash; Eliston, Avena, Brompton, The Avenue, Aspire,
          Riverdale and similar releases) are double-storey homes on 350&ndash;500m&sup2;
          blocks with double garages and a bedroom or home office directly above.
          The most common job here is a same-day spring repair on an
          8&ndash;14 year-old builder-grade door, often paired with a quiet
          belt-drive motor upgrade because the original chain-drive is waking
          the upstairs bedrooms.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Established Cranbourne</strong> (around the township, along
          South Gippsland Highway, Stawell Street, Berwick-Cranbourne Road)
          has plenty of 1980s&ndash;2000s single-garage brick veneer homes with
          tilt doors or first-generation sectionals on the way out. These are
          usually full-replacement jobs &mdash; new insulated sectional with a
          smart belt-drive opener, ~$2.5K&ndash;$5K supplied and installed.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Class M reactive-clay slab movement.</h3>
        <p>
          Cranbourne sits on Class M reactive clay. Garage slabs shift
          5&ndash;15mm seasonally on most blocks &mdash; over 10 years that
          adds up to noticeable track misalignment. Symptoms: door binding on
          one side, rubber bottom-seal not touching the slab, opener
          struggling at the same point of the lift each cycle. A 45-minute
          re-track-alignment ($180&ndash;$280) usually fixes it for another
          5&ndash;7 years.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Cranbourne jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Broken spring + cable on builder-grade double sectional &mdash; same-day repair ($350&ndash;$650)</li>
          <li>Quiet belt-drive motor swap on Cranbourne East estate home ($800&ndash;$1,400 fitted)</li>
          <li>New insulated Colorbond sectional double + smart Wi-Fi opener ($3,200&ndash;$5,000)</li>
          <li>Tilt-door replacement with sectional on established Cranbourne township home ($2,500&ndash;$4,200)</li>
          <li>Track re-alignment on a clay-shifted slab ($180&ndash;$280)</li>
          <li>Smart-home integration retrofit (Google Home / Alexa / HomeKit) on existing door ($300&ndash;$600)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-casey/">All City of Casey</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Same-day Cranbourne garage door call-out.</h2>
        <p>Broken spring? Quiet motor upgrade? New install? Local Cranbourne team, on the road in minutes.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
